{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DK1qUva88eqm5hMRYiFx7M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"Roster Application on Open Liberty\">\n     3→\n     4→    <featureManager>\n     5→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     6→    </featureManager>\n     7→\n     8→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9080\" httpsPort=\"9443\" />\n     9→\n    10→    <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"BasicRealm\">\n    11→        <user name=\"admin\" password=\"admin\" />\n    12→    </basicRegistry>\n    13→\n    14→    <!-- H2 Database DataSource Configuration -->\n    15→    <library id=\"h2Library\">\n    16→        <fileset dir=\"${shared.resource.dir}\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    17→    </library>\n    18→\n    19→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/__default\">\n    20→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Library\" javax.sql.DataSource=\"org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource\" />\n    21→        <properties url=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster\" />\n    22→    </dataSource>\n    23→\n    24→    <logging logDirectory=\"${server.output.dir}/logs\" />\n    25→\n    26→    <!-- Application configuration -->\n    27→    <enterpriseApplication id=\"roster-ear\" location=\"roster-ear-1.0.0.ear\" name=\"roster-ear\">\n    28→        <application-bnd>\n    29→            <security-role name=\"**\">\n    30→                <special-subject type=\"ALL_AUTHENTICATED_USERS\"/>\n    31→            </security-role>\n    32→        </application-bnd>\n    33→    </enterpriseApplication>\n    34→\n    35→</server>\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7aa9e9e3-b010-487c-a19d-8b03349f63ee","uuid":"3d44b446-f9f9-45ed-a8ef-8fdc7dd094bd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019m985ui7rRsKRxAvTKYsEh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<web-app xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     3→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee \n     5→         https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_6_0.xsd\"\n     6→         version=\"6.0\">\n     7→    \n     8→    <display-name>Roster Web Application</display-name>\n     9→    \n    10→    <welcome-file-list>\n    11→        <welcome-file>player.xhtml</welcome-file>\n    12→    </welcome-file-list>\n    13→    \n    14→    <context-param>\n    15→        <param-name>jakarta.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n    16→        <param-value>Production</param-value>\n    17→    </context-param>\n    18→    \n    19→    <context-param>\n    20→        <param-name>jakarta.faces.FACELETS_SKIP_COMMENTS</param-name>\n    21→        <param-value>true</param-value>\n    22→    </context-param>\n    23→    \n    24→    <servlet>\n    25→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    26→        <servlet-class>jakarta.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>\n    27→        <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>\n    28→    </servlet>\n    29→    \n    30→    <servlet-mapping>\n    31→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    32→        <url-pattern>*.xhtml</url-pattern>\n    33→    </servlet-mapping>\n    34→</web-app>\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7aa9e9e3-b010-487c-a19d-8b03349f63ee","uuid":"71fd9150-1f19-4685-a986-1656178b392d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ChnfaMppyju5FrK3jNSqQY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.roster.client;\n    13→\n    14→\n    15→import java.util.Iterator;\n    16→import java.util.List;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n    19→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n    20→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    21→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    22→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    23→\n    24→public class RosterClient {\n    25→    @EJB\n    26→    private static Request request;\n    27→    \n    28→    public RosterClient(String[] args) {\n    29→    }\n    30→\n    31→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    32→        RosterClient client = new RosterClient(args);\n    33→        try {\n    34→            client.insertInfo();\n    35→            client.getSomeInfo();\n    36→            client.getMoreInfo();\n    37→            client.removeInfo();\n    38→\n    39→            System.exit(0);\n    40→\n    41→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    42→            System.err.println(\"Caught an exception:\");\n    43→        }\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    private void insertInfo() {\n    47→\n    48→        try {\n    49→            // Leagues\n    50→            request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\", \"Mountain\", \"Soccer\"));\n    51→            request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L2\", \"Valley\", \"Basketball\"));\n    52→            request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L3\", \"Foothills\", \"Soccer\"));\n    53→            request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L4\", \"Alpine\", \"Snowboarding\"));\n    54→\n    55→            // Teams\n    56→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T1\", \"Honey Bees\", \"Visalia\"), \n    57→                    \"L1\");\n    58→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T2\", \"Gophers\", \"Manteca\"),\n    59→                    \"L1\");\n    60→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T5\", \"Crows\", \"Orland\"),\n    61→                    \"L1\");\n    62→            \n    63→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T3\", \"Deer\", \"Bodie\"),\n    64→                    \"L2\");\n    65→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T4\", \"Trout\", \"Truckee\"),\n    66→                    \"L2\");\n    67→            \n    68→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T6\", \"Marmots\", \"Auburn\"),\n    69→                    \"L3\");\n    70→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T7\", \"Bobcats\", \"Grass Valley\"), \n    71→                    \"L3\");\n    72→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T8\", \"Beavers\", \"Placerville\"), \n    73→                    \"L3\");\n    74→            \n    75→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T9\", \"Penguins\", \"Incline Village\"),\n    76→                    \"L4\");\n    77→            request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T10\", \"Land Otters\", \"Tahoe City\"),\n    78→                    \"L4\");\n    79→\n    80→            // Players, Team T1\n    81→            request.createPlayer(\"P1\", \"Phil Jones\", \"goalkeeper\", 100.00);\n    82→            request.addPlayer(\"P1\", \"T1\");\n    83→\n    84→            request.createPlayer(\"P2\", \"Alice Smith\", \"defender\", 505.00);\n    85→            request.addPlayer(\"P2\", \"T1\");\n    86→\n    87→       